                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1390.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>227. Some isolated cases of violence and robbery by irresponsible bands took
                    place in suburbs during first two days against Mexicans and foreigners
                    indiscriminately, including Americans, but the cases have been punished, in some
                    instances even with execution of culprits, the Zapatista authorities always
                    trying their best redress the damage done. Minister of Spain as much if not more
                    than all other colleagues is being attended in his requests to the point of
                    having obtained a safe conduct in favor of Consul of Spain, ordering everybody
                    to obey and help him in his work in behalf of Spaniards. A general order from
                    Villa published to the effect that full guarantees be accorded to all, any wrong
                    to be punished by death.</p>
                <p>Up to the present moment and if things do not change by unforeseen circumstances,
                    general situation in the capital can be now considered as surprisingly good.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
